based burgers require 96% less land, 87% less water, and 89% less greenhouse emissions to produce than traditional burgers. Their mission is to produce plant based meat in order to reduce the impact of the meat industry on the environment.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T09:38:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"nglgzz/awesome-clean-tech","categoryHTML":"<h2>Companies</h2><h3>Food</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.happycow.net/\">HappyCow</a> | California, USA | 1999</p>\n<p>Reduce or avoid meat entirely by finding great vegetarian or vegan food all over the world.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T09:38:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"nglgzz/awesome-clean-tech","categoryHTML":"<h2>Companies</h2><h3>Food</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://new.karma.life/\">Karma</a> | Sweden | 2016</p>\n<p>Helps restaurants, cafes, and grocery stores selling their surplus food at a discounted price. As a result, users get food for less and businesses receive an additional revenue stream — all while reducing food waste.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T09:38:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"nglgzz/awesome-clean-tech","categoryHTML":"<h2>Companies</h2><h3>Food</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://olioex.com/\">Olio</a> | UK | 2015</p>\n<p>Mobile app for food-sharing, aiming to reduce food waste. It does this by connecting those with surplus food to those who need or wish to consume such food. The food must be edible; it can be raw or cooked, sealed or open.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T09:38:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"nglgzz/awesome-clean-tech","categoryHTML":"<h2>Companies</h2><h3>Food</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://toogoodtogo.com/en\">Too Good To Go</a> | France | 2016</p>\n<p>Gives the possibility for restaurants, stores, bakeries and cafés to sell unsold food at the end of the day. Since it is impossible to know in advance what will be the unsolds of the day, the users get a \"surprise basket\" of about 500g of food. Pretty much like Karma, but more present in France.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T09:38:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.manning.com/books/succeeding-with-ai\">Succeeding with AI</a> - An introduction to managing successful AI projects and applying AI to real-life situations.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T09:37:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"simskij/awesome-software-architecture","categoryHTML":"<h2>Methodology</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Clean-Architecture-Craftsmans-Software-Structure/dp/0134494164\">Clean Architecture, by Martin</a> - Key principles and concepts for building sustainable and maintainable software 📙.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T08:10:43.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"simskij/awesome-software-architecture","categoryHTML":"<h2>Methodology</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=URSWYvyc42M\">The Magic Tricks of Testing, by Metz</a> - Minimalistic ideals as a practical and pragmatic approach to software testing 🎥.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T08:10:43.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"simskij/awesome-software-architecture","categoryHTML":"<h2>Methodology</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.infoq.com/presentations/tdd-original/\">TDD, Where did it all go wrong?, by Cooper</a> - Suggestion on TDD practices and boundaries to reduce coupling 🎥.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T08:10:43.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"avelino/awesome-go","categoryHTML":"<h2>Distributed Systems</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/liftbridge-io/liftbridge\">liftbridge</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/liftbridge-io/liftbridge\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;backgr